com.apriori.collections

Interface ImmutableCollection<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of element in the collection
    All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<E>, SizedIterable<E>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ImmutableList<E>, ImmutableSet<E>, ImmutableSortedSet<E>, PersistentCollection<E>, PersistentList<E>, PersistentSet<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractImmutableCollection, AbstractImmutableSet, AbstractLinkedImmutableList, AbstractLinkedImmutableList.LinkedSubList, AbstractRandomAccessImmutableList, AbstractRandomAccessImmutableList.SubList, AmtPersistentList, HamtPersistentSet, LinkedPersistentList

    public interface ImmutableCollection<E>
extends SizedIterable<E>
    An immutable, read-only collection. This interface is similar to the standard Collection interface except that it defines no mutation operations.

    The remove() operation of an immutable collection's Iterable.iterator() always throws UnsupportedOperationException.

      • toArray

        Object[] toArray()
        Returns an array with the same elements as this collection. The order of elements in the returned array is the same as the order that elements are returned by the collection's Iterable.iterator().
        Returns:
        an array with the same elements as this collection
        See Also:
        Collection.toArray()

      • toArray

        <T> T[] toArray(T[] array)
        Returns an array with the same elements as this collection and the same component type as the specified array. If the elements will fit in the specified array, they are copied there and a null terminator is stored after the elements if the array can hold more. Otherwise, a new array with the same element type is allocated, and the elements are copied into it.
        Parameters:
        array - an array
        Returns:
        an array with the same elements as this collection and the same component type as the specified array (possibly the same instance as the one specified)
        Throws:
        ArrayStoreException - if any of the elements are not assignable to the component type of the specified array
        See Also:
        Collection.toArray(Object[])
